For anyone following this topic (feels like none):  I have updated information concerning the XP machine.  Yesterday I had to re-register those DLL files and reboot so that the machine could &quot;sync&quot; license data online with Intuit for a new installation (upgraded) of QB Pro 2014.  <img src="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":-(" title="Sad" /><br /><br />  I have not yet gone back and unregistered those dll files, but I am feeling like keeping them as not registered may be a good proactive route.<br /><br />  Also on my own machine (still has not been rebooted since unregistering them) I was not able to visit a site.  I tested the link from another machine and it came right up, so I do suspect unregistering these dll files WILL create problems.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=21701">RSexton</a> — Tue May 12, 2015 9:59 am</p><hr />
